sql:
SELECT stocks.name, predictions.prediction_method
FROM stocks
INNER JOIN predictions ON stocks.stock_id = predictions.stock_id;

external_knowledge:
- S&P 500 refers to the S&P 500 stock market index, which is a market-capitalization-weighted index of the 500 largest publicly traded companies in the US; 
- A medium news relevance implies that the news articles have a moderate impact or significance to the stock; 
- Split ratios above 2 indicate that the stock has undergone a stock split, where the number of shares has increased while the total value remains the same.
